Sustainable Quality

min(EOM) = Expansion of Morbidity min(EOHE) = Expansion of Health Expenditure

df.sust <- data.frame(COUNTRY=df.EU.2010$country)

df.sust$EOM <- round(((df.EU.2010$yld - df.EU.1990$yld) / (df.EU.2010$hale - df.EU.1990$hale)) * (df.EU.1990$hale / df.EU.1990$yld), 2)

df.sust$EOHE <- round(((df.EU.2010$the - df.EU.1990$the) / (df.EU.2010$le - df.EU.1990$le)) * (df.EU.1990$le / df.EU.1990$the), 2)

df.sust$SusQ <-  df.sust$EOM + df.sust$EOHE

df.sust$RANK <- rank(df.sust$SusQ)

df.sust <- df.sust[order(df.sust$RANK), ]

ID.EU <- df.sust$country[df.sust$RANK == 1]
